 encryption is the standard method for protecting passwords. If passwords are not encrypted, they can be plainly read (i.e., clear text) and easily compromised.\n\nlink:https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/opendirectory\/kodattributetypeauthenticationauthority[]\n"},"os_ssh_fips_compliant":{"result":{"integer":"8"},"excluded":true,"mobileconfig":false,"id":"os_ssh_fips_compliant","title":"Limit SSH to FIPS Compliant Connections","fix":"[source,bash]\n----\nfips_ssh_config=\"Host *\nCiphers aes128-gcm@openssh.com\nHostbasedAcceptedAlgorithms ecdsa-sha2-nistp256,ecdsa-sha2-nistp256-cert-v01@openssh.com\nHostKeyAlgorithms ecdsa-sha2-nistp256,ecdsa-sha2-nistp256-cert-v01@openssh.com\nKexAlgorithms ecdh-sha2-nistp256\nMACs hmac-sha2-256\nPubkeyAcceptedAlgorithms ecdsa-sha2-nistp256,ecdsa-sha2-nistp256-cert-v01@openssh.com\nCASignatureAlgorithms ecdsa-sha2-nistp256\"\n\/bin\/echo \"${fips_ssh_config}\" > \/etc\/ssh\/ssh_config.d\/fips_ssh_config\n----\n","check":"fips_ssh_config=\"Host *\nCiphers aes128-gcm@openssh.com\nHostbasedAcceptedAlgorithms ecdsa-sha2-nistp256,ecdsa-sha2-nistp256-cert-v01@openssh.com\nHostKeyAlgorithms ecdsa-sha2-nistp256,ecdsa-sha2-nistp256-cert-v01@openssh.com\nKexAlgorithms ecdh-sha2-nistp256\nMACs hmac-sha2-256\nPubkeyAcceptedAlgorithms ecdsa-sha2-nistp256,ecdsa-sha2-nistp256-cert-v01@openssh.com\nCASignatureAlgorithms ecdsa-sha2-nistp256\"\n\/usr\/bin\/grep -c \"$fips_ssh_config\" \/etc\/ssh\/ssh_config.d\/fips_ssh_config\n","references":{"srg":["SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","SRG-OS-000120-GPOS-00061","SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","SRG-OS-000478-GPOS-00223","SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014","SRG-OS-000396-GPOS-00176"],"800-171r2":["3.1.13","3.13.8","3.13.11"],"800-53r4":["AC-17(2)","IA-7","SC-8(1)","SC-13"],"disa_stig":["APPL-14-000057"],"cce":["CCE-92894-5"],"800-53r5":["AC-17(2)","IA-7","SC-13","SC-8(1)"],"cci":["CCI-000068","CCI-000803","CCI-001453","CCI-002421","CCI-002450"],"cmmc":["AC.L2-3.1.13","MP.L2-3.8.6","SC.L2-3.13.8","SC.L2-3.13.11"]},"discussion":"SSH _MUST_ be configured to limit the Ciphers, HostbasedAcceptedAlgorithms, HostKeyAlgorithms, KexAlgorithms, MACs, PubkeyAcceptedAlgorithms, CASignatureAlgorithms to algorithms that are FIPS 140 validated.\n\nFIPS 140-2 is the current standard for validating that mechanisms used to access cryptographic modules utilize authentication that meet federal requirements.\n\nOperating systems utilizing encryption _MUST_ use FIPS validated mechanisms for authenticating to cryptographic modules.\n\nNOTE: For more information on FIPS compliance with the version of SSH included in the macOS, the manual page apple_ssh_and_fips has additional information.\n","tags":["800-53r5_moderate","800-53r5_high","800-53r5_low","800-53r4_low","800-53r4_moderate","800-53r4_high","800-171","cnssi-1253_moderate","cnssi-1253_low","cnssi-1253_high","cmmc_lvl2","stig"]},"icloud_freeform_disable":{"result":{"string":"false"},"excluded":true,"mobileconfig":true,"id":"icloud_freeform_disable","mobileconfiginfo":"  com.apple.applicationaccess:\n    allowCloudFreeform: false\n","title":"Disable the iCloud Freeform Services","fix":"This is implemented by a Configuration Profile.\n","check":"\/usr\/bin\/osascript -l JavaScript << EOS\n$.NSUserDefaults.alloc.initWithSuiteName('com.apple.applicationaccess')\\\n.objectForKey('allowCloudFreeform').js\nEOS\n","references":{"srg":["SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"],"800-171r2":["3.1.20","3.4.6"],"800-53r4":["CM-7","CM-7(1)","AC-20","AC-20(1)"],"disa_stig":["APPL-14-002270"],"cis":{"benchmark":["N\/A"],"controls v8":["4.1","4.8","15.3"]},"cce":["CCE-92746-7"],"cmmc":["AC.L1-3.1.20","CM.L2-3.4.6","CM.L2-3.4.7"],"800-53r5":["AC-20","AC-20(1)","CM-7","CM-7(1)","SC-7(10)"],"cci":["CCI-000381","CCI-001774"]},"tags":["800-53r5_low","800-53r5_moderate","800-53r5_high","800-53r4_low","800-53r4_moderate","800-53r4_high","800-171","cisv8","cnssi-1253_moderate","cnssi-1253_low","cnssi-1253_high","cmmc_lvl2","cmmc_lvl1","stig"],"discussion":"The macOS built-in Fre