rictions, including failed file write (-fw) attempts.\n\nEnforcement actions are the methods or mechanisms used to prevent unauthorized access and\/or changes to configuration settings. One common and effective enforcement action method is using access restrictions (e.g., denying users access to edit a file by applying file permissions).\n\nThis configuration ensures that audit lists include events in which enforcement actions prevent attempts to change a file.\n\nWithout auditing the enforcement of access restrictions, it is difficult to identify attempted attacks, as there is no audit trail available for forensic investigation.\n","tags":["800-53r5_privacy","800-53r4_low","800-53r4_moderate","800-53r4_high","800-53r5_low","800-53r5_moderate","800-53r5_high","800-171","cis_lvl2","cisv8","cnssi-1253_moderate","cnssi-1253_low","cnssi-1253_high","cmmc_lvl2","stig"]},"pwpolicy_custom_regex_enforce":{"id":"pwpolicy_custom_regex_enforce","fix":"This is implemented by a Configuration Profile.\n","check":"\/usr\/bin\/pwpolicy -getaccountpolicies 2> \/dev\/null | \/usr\/bin\/tail +2 | \/usr\/bin\/xmllint --xpath 'boolean(\/\/*[contains(text(),\"policyAttributePassword matches '\\''$ODV'\\''\")])' -\n","tags":["800-171","800-53r4_low","800-53r4_moderate","800-53r4_high","800-53r5_low","800-53r5_moderate","800-53r5_high","cis_lvl2","cisv8","cnssi-1253_moderate","cnssi-1253_low","cnssi-1253_high","cmmc_lvl2","stig"],"customOdv":"^(?=.*[A-Z])(?=.*[a-z]).*$","title":"Require Passwords to Match the Defined Custom Regular Expression","excluded":true,"mobileconfiginfo":"  com.apple.mobiledevice.passwordpolicy:\n    customRegex:\n      passwordContentRegex: $ODV\n      passwordContentDescription:\n        default: Password must match custom regex.\n","odv":{"recommended":"^(?=.*[A-Z])(?=.*[a-z]).*$","cis_lvl2":"^(?=.*[A-Z])(?=.*[a-z]).*$","stig":"^(?=.*[A-Z])(?=.*[a-z]).*$","hint":"Custom regex (recommended is 1 upper and 1 lowercase)"},"discussion":"The macOS _MUST_ be configured t